<TITLE> 3 burnt alive in Satkania road accident </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Feb 10 (bdnews24.com)  Three people were burnt alive after a microbus caught fire on the Chittagong-Cox's Bazar highway on Wednesday morning, police said. Eight people were also injured in the incident. They were admitted to Chittagong Medical College Hospital. The dead could not be identified immediately. The Cox's Bazar bound microbus lost control, hit a roadside tree and caught fire near Kerani Haat at Satkania upazila at around 7am, said Mahim Uddin Masud, sub-inspector of Satkania Police Station. 
